text.section:
The budget books shall contain a section that, by unit of the State government, sets forth, for each program or purpose of that unit:
the total number of officers and employees and the number in each job classification:
authorized in the State budget for the last full fiscal year and the current fiscal year; and
requested for the next fiscal year;
the total amount for salaries of officers and employees and the amount for salaries of each job classification:
spent during the last full fiscal year;
authorized in the State budget for the current fiscal year; and
requested for the next fiscal year;
an itemized statement of the expenditures for contractual services, supplies and materials, equipment, land and structures, fixed charges, and other operating expenses:
made in the last full fiscal year;
authorized in the State budget for the current fiscal year; and
requested for the next fiscal year; and
the StateStat or managing for results agency strategic plan required under this article that shall be limited to a description of the agency's mission, goals, objectives, and performance measures.

In its annual submission of the proposed budget, the Department of Budget and Management shall provide, for informational purposes, a budget presentation that includes a description of the proposed expenditures under the Maryland Emergency Medical System Operations Fund for the:
Maryland Institute for Emergency Medical Services Systems;
R Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center;
Maryland Fire and Rescue Institute;
Aviation Division of the Special Operations Bureau, Department of State Police; and
grants under the Senator William H. Amoss Fire, Rescue, and Ambulance Fund.

section.section:
The budget books shall contain a budget presentation that provides an overview of the proposed expenditures for:
the Tobacco Program, including the proposed expenditures for:
each Component of the Tobacco Program;
each program funded under each Component of the Tobacco Program; and
each Local Public Health Tobacco Grant;
the Cancer Program, including the proposed expenditures for:
each Component of the Cancer Program;
each program funded under each Component of the Cancer Program;
each Local Public Health Cancer Grant;
each statewide Academic Health Center Public Health Grant;
each statewide Academic Health Center Cancer Research Grant;
each statewide Academic Health Center Tobacco-Related Diseases Research Grant; and
each statewide Academic Health Center Network Grant; and
any other program that is funded with the Cigarette Restitution Fund established under § 7-317 of this title.
